===Noun===
'''bacterium''' (Plural: [[bacteria]])

# a single celled organism with no [[nucleus]] or [[organelle]]s

====Usage note====
*This is the singular form of the word.  While the plural '''bacteria''' is often used as if it were the singular, this is incorrect.  See the examples below.
*'''Correct usage'''
*:''Scientists have discovered a bacterium that infects cattle.''
*:''There are millions of bacteria on every square inch of your skin.''
*'''Incorrect usage'''
*:''* The common cold is caused by a virus, not a bacteria.''
*:''* The bacteria in the wound causes infection.''

